but when Mali doesn’t play,
they keep a low profile.

1:17:06.115 --> 1:17:08.028
Weird.

1:17:08.243 --> 1:17:11.245
So, whether Mali plays in the
African Cup of Nations or not,

1:17:11.246 --> 1:17:15.011
...the Africans in this class
feel more or less African. Ok.

1:17:17.544 --> 1:17:19.766
Thank you, Nassim.

1:17:20.548 --> 1:17:23.633
I get the feeling
your words are directed

1:17:23.634 --> 1:17:25.427
...at your neighbor, Souleymane

1:17:25.428 --> 1:17:26.887
Morocco jerk's

1:17:26.888 --> 1:17:28.432
...not even on my radar,

1:17:30.058 --> 1:17:32.485
Arthur is next

1:17:35.939 --> 1:17:39.317
I see you have your notes
just like a politician

1:17:39.318 --> 1:17:41.277
- Exactly
- That's good

1:17:41.278 --> 1:17:44.614
Speak up Arthur.
Esmeralda, let him speak first

1:17:44.615 --> 1:17:46.408
I want to defend my look

1:17:46.409 --> 1:17:51.363
...A lot of people say it sucks

1:17:51.748 --> 1:17:57.176
I don’t dish your clothes,
so you don’t dish mine.

1:17:58.130 --> 1:18:00.454
Clothes are freedom of speech

1:18:00.966 --> 1:18:05.137
I dress how I want
you dress how you want, ok

1:18:05.138 --> 1:18:07.723
I dress like this to be different

1:18:07.724 --> 1:18:10.893
...and not follow the others
like sheep.

1:18:10.894 --> 1:18:13.771
You're the sheep here!

1:18:13.772 --> 1:18:17.567
I feel better being myself

1:18:17.568 --> 1:18:19.421
and not being like others

1:18:21.739 --> 1:18:25.450
I also think
if there were 22 goths here,

1:18:25.451 --> 1:18:28.494
...and one guy like you
you'd keep quiet then

1:18:29.998 --> 1:18:33.167
There's a contradiction
in what you say

1:18:33.168 --> 1:18:36.003
You want to be you.
Are those clothes you?

1:18:36.004 --> 1:18:40.258
Those clothes are worn
by a huge number of people

1:18:40.259 --> 1:18:43.595
Most people who wear them
are gloomy inside

1:18:43.596 --> 1:18:46.473
...so we're all kind of alike

1:18:46.474 --> 1:18:50.936
- You're all alike, you're all gloomy,
so that’s not you.

1:18:50.937 --> 1:18:53.564
By being different

1:18:53.565 --> 1:18:55.933
You're different and the same.

1:18:56.276 --> 1:18:58.528
Thank you for taking a stand

1:18:58.529 --> 1:19:01.839
...and being brave enough to do so

1:19:01.866 --> 1:19:03.658
Boubacar, go on

1:19:03.659 --> 1:19:06.292
Boubacar, my pal

1:19:06.537 --> 1:19:08.450
Listen to him

1:19:10.917 --> 1:19:12.667
I’ve come up to reply to Nassim

1:19:13.879 --> 1:19:16.339
He says that since Mali

1:19:16.340 --> 1:19:21.553
isn’t in the Africa Cup of Nations
black Africans have no team to support

1:19:21.554 --> 1:19:23.972
But he's forgetting Ivory Coast!

1:19:23.973 --> 1:19:26.915
With an ace player Didier Drogba

1:19:27.185 --> 1:19:31.480
He beats any Moroccan

1:19:31.481 --> 1:19:34.692
He plays for Chelsea
What Moroccan plays in England?

1:19:34.693 --> 1:19:36.036
They're not up to it

1:19:36.487 --> 1:19:39.155
I'm through.

1:19:39.156 --> 1:19:40.500
Thanks, Boubacar

1:19:40.866 --> 1:19:43.852
I think that rectification
was indeed...

1:19:44.412 --> 1:19:46.426
...indispensable

1:19:48.208 --> 1:19:50.429
Who wants to speak now?

1:19:50.543 --> 1:19:52.293
Carl, go on

1:19:58.928 --> 1:20:00.887
Actually, I'd like to say

1:20:00.888 --> 1:20:03.181
they're starting to piss us off...

1:20:03.182 --> 1:20:05.767
...with the Africa Cup

1:20:05.768 --> 1:20:09.146
At recess you're there
pissing us off with your cup

1:20:09.147 --> 1:20:11.565
It hasn't even started yet...

1:20:11.566 --> 1:20:14.360
Carl, I'll be polite with you

1:20:14.361 --> 1:20:18.406
Sorry to interrupt, but tell me,
what's your national team?

1:20:18.407 --> 1:20:19.750
France

1:20:20.910 --> 1:20:23.578
Why do you say you're Caribbean...

1:20:23.579 --> 1:20:25.205
...rather than French?

1:20:25.206 --> 1:20:28.766
We're French. It's a French region

1:20:29.461 --> 1:20:31.796
Why don't you ever say
you're French?

1:20:31.797 --> 1:20:33.965
- It's the same
- I don't think so

1:20:33.966 --> 1:20:37.093
Look at the players.
Thierry Henri, Wiltord...

1:20:37.094 --> 1:20:39.256
...Abidal, Thuram...

1:20:39.263 --> 1:20:41.473
Where does Diarra play?

1:20:41.474 --> 1:20:44.935
He won't play in Mali, bro,
he's not crazy enough.

1:20:44.936 --> 1:20:48.522
Shut your mouth, pal,
I'm not your bro!

1:20:48.523 --> 1:20:50.994
An ape like this jerk

1:20:52.235 --> 1:20:54.662
No need to loose your cool.

1:20:56.907 --> 1:20:59.378
We can talk calmly!

1:21:00.995 --> 1:21:04.414
That isn’t a slanging match.
It’s a debate.

1:21:04.415 --> 1:21:07.376
Souleymane,
watch your language

1:21:07.377 --> 1:21:08.710
He's fuming!

1:21:08.711 --> 1:21:11.338
Clam up. Go get fucked!

1:21:11.339 --> 1:21:13.549
No vulgarity

1:21:13.550 --> 1:21:16.434
- I ain’t talking to you, man
- I’m talking to you

1:21:16.470 --> 1:21:18.999
Is that any way
to talk to a teacher?

1:21:21.475 --> 1:21:25.479
That's enough now
You're coming with me

1:21:25.480 --> 1:21:29.305
- I'm talking to you
- Don't start yelling at me, ok

1:21:31.319 --> 1:21:33.279
I'll get you, faggot

1:21:33.280 --> 1:21:35.647
You just can’t talk normally?

1:21:35.741 --> 1:21:37.575
Shut up, ape

1:21:37.576 --> 1:21:39.164
Nobody else moves

1:21:56.054 --> 1:21:58.011
Hurry it up

1:22:01.060 --> 1:22:03.943
- Move it
- Hands off!

1:22:17.911 --> 1:22:21.103
Aren’t you sick
of assing around?

1:22:30.675 --> 1:22:32.117
Sorry to bother you

1:22:32.135 --> 1:22:37.564
I have a troublemaker who's
been disrespectful in class.

1:22:40.436 --> 1:22:44.201
I didn’t ask you to sit down,
Souleymane.

1:22:48.820 --> 1:22:52.071
My class is waiting

1:23:01.417 --> 1:23:03.226
Sit down now.

1:23:09.551 --> 1:23:11.669
I'm listening

1:23:15.849 --> 1:23:18.688
Will you tell me what happened?

1:23:19.103 --> 1:23:24.369
A teacher should have to leave
his class to bring you here?

1:23:31.658 --> 1:23:33.880
"Results

1:23:34.036 --> 1:23:36.154
..."too uneven

1:23:36.622 --> 1:23:39.049
"Too much talking in class"

1:23:44.213 --> 1:23:46.924
Now let's move on to Louise,

1:23:46.925 --> 1:23:48.837
present here today

1:23:50.053 --> 1:23:52.480
A total disaster.
What can we do with you?

1:23:52.848 --> 1:23:54.056
No, good work

1:23:54.057 --> 1:23:55.975
Always good, I'd say

1:23:55.976 --> 1:24:01.134
It's a joy having a student
like her. We need to say it.

1:24:01.399 --> 1:24:05.736
Shall we offer this young lady
a commendation?

1:24:05.737 --> 1:24:07.029
I'm sorry, but I don't

1:24:07.030 --> 1:24:09.239
...totally agree with you.

1:24:09.240 --> 1:24:12.535
She's relatively well-placed
in the class

1:24:12.536 --> 1:24:15.005
from a numerical angle

1:24:15.497 --> 1:24:18.166
But a commendation?
There's room for progress,

1:24:18.167 --> 1:24:21.127
huge room for progress

1:24:21.128 --> 1:24:24.089
and I don’t think
her general attitude

1:24:24.090 --> 1:24:26.550
...really merits a commendation

1:24:26.551 --> 1:24:27.759
That's the problem

1:24:27.760 --> 1:24:29.845
with commendations

1:24:29.846 --> 1:24:33.808
...Are they purely numerical
and mathematical

1:24:33.809 --> 1:24:35.309
or are they also to do

1:24:35.310 --> 1:24:39.341
...with her attitude and behavior
as top of the class?

1:24:39.356 --> 1:24:42.317
That means, to get commendation,

1:24:42.318 --> 1:24:45.529
...you have to be an excellent student

1:24:45.530 --> 1:24:49.046
...and, at the same time,
be a class leader?

1:24:53.038 --> 1:24:55.665
So a commendation this term

1:24:55.666 --> 1:24:59.544
Louise is intelligent

1:24:59.545 --> 1:25:02.352
...and will realize she can do better
to satisfy you

1:25:07.512 --> 1:25:10.498
Now, Cherif

1:25:10.515 --> 1:25:12.266
...Our friend Cherif

1:25:12.267 --> 1:25:15.228
I have a problem with Cherif

1:25:15.229 --> 1:25:17.438
...He's a kid with abilities
he could do well

1:25:17.439 --> 1:25:20.150
could easily give him 17/20

1:25:20.151 --> 1:25:22.569
...but he spends so much time talking

1:25:22.570 --> 1:25:25.864
...and disturbing the class,

1:25:25.865 --> 1:25:28.325
...his average grade is poor
And that's a pity

1:25:28.326 --> 1:25:30.870
His behavior's irregular.
He can be a disaster

1:25:30.871 --> 1:25:35.208
and you cant do a thing with him

1:25:35.209 --> 1:25:37.738
or he can be really good

1:25:37.836 --> 1:25:41.339
- What does Cherif get?
A warning about his work

1:25:41.340 --> 1:25:42.883
or his behavior?

1:25:42.884 --> 1:25:44.325
For me, behavior,

1:25:44.343 --> 1:25:45.108
...not work

1:25:45.219 --> 1:25:48.470
- In my class, it's more his work
- That’s a problem.

1:25:48.765 --> 1:25:51.642
It's more like a work problem
looking at his grades.

1:25:51.643 --> 1:25:53.805
Mathematics: 6

1:25:54.897 --> 1:25:56.382
French: 8

1:25:58.567 --> 1:26:01.142
History and geography: 9

1:26:01.278 --> 1:26:04.402
English: 9,5

1:26:04.532 --> 1:26:05.875
Excuse me!

1:26:09.079 --> 1:26:11.872
Science 12. Music 11

1:26:11.873 --> 1:26:14.834
His grades are pretty low but...

1:26:14.835 --> 1:26:18.296
...it seems to be a behavior problem

1:26:18.297 --> 1:26:21.466
Why don't we put that for now
and say he can work harder?

1:26:21.467 --> 1:26:23.732
So I'll put Cherif

1:26:23.970 --> 1:26:27.431
"..." can succeed as long as

1:26:27.432 --> 1:26:30.351
"..." his attitude changes

1:26:30.352 --> 1:26:32.161
... " in relation to his work."

1:26:36.400 --> 1:26:38.902
Let's move on to Souleymane

1:26:38.903 --> 1:26:42.933
Someone else can start.

1:26:43.366 --> 1:26:44.699
What do we say?

1:26:44.700 --> 1:26:46.326
Nothing good.

1:26:46.327 --> 1:26:50.539
- What else?
- We already discussed him

1:26:50.540 --> 1:26:54.752
in the first term. We said it all
He has huge weakness,

1:26:54.753 --> 1:26:56.712
notably in written French

1:26:56.713 --> 1:27:02.218
I don’t think there’s anything
particularly new

1:27:02.219 --> 1:27:03.720
this term

1:27:03.721 --> 1:27:05.153
Feeling better, Esmeralda?

1:27:06.099 --> 1:27:10.026
I didn’t know being class rep
was such fun

1:27:10.145 --> 1:27:12.521
We were talking about Souleymane

1:27:12.522 --> 1:27:13.648
In relation

1:27:13.649 --> 1:27:16.192
to what Francois just said,

1:27:16.193 --> 1:27:21.281
he forgot his things
most of the time this term

1:27:21.282 --> 1:27:23.238
...and didn’t do much

1:27:23.701 --> 1:27:25.848
It’s not just that,
It’s way beyond that

1:27:26.120 --> 1:27:27.606
Sir!

1:27:27.622 --> 1:27:33.044
He’s more and more unruly
He prevents the others from working.

1:27:33.045 --> 1:27:34.378
Can I say something?

1:27:34.379 --> 1:27:36.172
If you put the biscuit away.

1:27:36.173 --> 1:27:41.302
Remember, you aren’t allowed
to eat in classroom

1:27:41.303 --> 1:27:47.303
Well, his overall grade
has gone from 6,75 to 7,25.

1:27:49.270 --> 1:27:52.773
We're not discussing his grades

1:27:52.774 --> 1:27:54.817
...but his behavior for now

1:27:54.818 --> 1:27:56.260
I have the impression

1:27:56.945 --> 1:27:59.989
...we need to consider
disciplinary action

1:27:59.990 --> 1:28:02.075
His attitude's wrong

1:28:02.076 --> 1:28:05.954
It's simple. Every other class
I throw him out

1:28:05.955 --> 1:28:09.500
I don’t even throw
him out anymore,

1:28:09.501 --> 1:28:12.878
...He’s only too happy when I do.

1:28:12.879 --> 1:28:16.382
I don’t think disciplinary action
will help...

1:28:16.383 --> 1:28:17.825
...because things will get

1:28:17.843 --> 1:28:19.677
...really bad then

1:28:19.678 --> 1:28:23.640
They’re already really bad
It’s gone too far.

1:28:23.641 --> 1:28:28.186
It’s like he’s mad at the others
for being normal

1:28:28.188 --> 1:28:29.855
I'll remind you Mr. Marin

1:28:29.856 --> 1:28:33.783
...you brought him to me yesterday.

1:28:33.819 --> 1:28:36.946
Yes, but it was this year's
first incident.

1:28:36.947 --> 1:28:40.617
He was disrespectful, I set a limit

1:28:40.618 --> 1:28:43.161
I did what I did but I don’t think

1:28:43.162 --> 1:28:46.575
it will go any further than that

1:28:47.292 --> 1:28:50.002
I don’t have any real complaints,

1:28:50.003 --> 1:28:51.837
...apart from yesterday

1:28:51.838 --> 1:28:53.965
Our job isn't to make sure

1:28:53.966 --> 1:28:58.094
students sit quietly at the back
and don’t cause any trouble.

1:28:58.095 --> 1:29:00.360
We have to bring them out!

1:29:00.723 --> 1:29:04.184
I won’t do that
with threats or punishment,

1:29:04.185 --> 1:29:08.313
...I'd rather stress his good work.
Some things interest him.

1:29:08.314 --> 1:29:11.275
He can come out
with some pretty good stuff

1:29:11.276 --> 1:29:12.568
Simply because he does

1:29:12.569 --> 1:29:15.349
...something positive now and then,

1:29:16.156 --> 1:29:19.409
...we let him sink
and wallow in his hole...

1:29:19.410 --> 1:29:23.337
...and we do nothing. You
just want to buy social harmony.

1:29:27.043 --> 1:29:28.425
That said,

1:29:28.461 --> 1:29:32.639
what do we say? What do we do?
A warning?

1:29:33.008 --> 1:29:36.135
I don’t think a warnings
what he needs.

1:29:36.136 --> 1:29:40.473
Maybe we should say
he has reached his limit,

1:29:40.474 --> 1:29:43.828
...because he’s
limited scholastically.

1:29:50.026 --> 1:29:53.654
That’s all well and good
but I’m dim and have a line to fill.

1:29:53.655 --> 1:29:55.508
What do we put?

1:29:56.575 --> 1:29:57.957
It’s not right

1:29:57.993 --> 1:29:59.641
...saying that

1:30:07.879 --> 1:30:12.133
Three rhymes per verse.
What do you call that?

1:30:12.134 --> 1:30:13.592
- Verses of three lines... Wey?
- A tercet

1:30:13.593 --> 1:30:15.711
Very good

1:30:16.013 --> 1:30:18.587
And four rhymes would be?

1:30:19.058 --> 1:30:20.543
A quatrain

1:30:21.227 --> 1:30:22.894
From quatre, four

1:30:22.895 --> 1:30:25.480
Tercet, three rhymes.
Quatrain, four

1:30:25.481 --> 1:30:28.358
How many syllabes per line?

1:30:28.359 --> 1:30:29.902
Can you tell me that?
Khoumba.

1:30:29.903 --> 1:30:31.285
I know here are 10

1:30:31.571 --> 1:30:32.905
You know that?

1:30:32.906 --> 1:30:34.615
- Want me to show you?
- Yes.

1:30:34.616 --> 1:30:36.659
"Noir-dans-la-nei-ge...

1:30:36.660 --> 1:30:38.828
... "et-dans-la-bru-me."

1:30:38.829 --> 1:30:40.580
Thats 10

1:30:40.581 --> 1:30:43.083
You say that and...

1:30:43.084 --> 1:30:45.377
...You have two

1:30:45.378 --> 1:30:49.512
...extra syllables
by counting the mute Es.

1:30:49.591 --> 1:30:52.842
Don’t count them, they’re mute

1:30:54.054 --> 1:30:56.790
That makes 8

1:30:56.890 --> 1:30:59.361
...We can underline each syllable

1:30:59.852 --> 1:31:01.936
I'll come back to that one

1:31:01.937 --> 1:31:03.855
Two octosyllables
and one four-syllable line

1:31:03.856 --> 1:31:06.024
- What is it?
- A problem,

1:31:06.025 --> 1:31:08.444
11.47 that makes

1:31:08.445 --> 1:31:09.930
11,5.

1:31:10.155 --> 1:31:11.906
Is 11.47 the number of syllables here?

1:31:11.907 --> 1:31:14.992
No, my grade. It's down!
They lowered my grade!

1:31:14.993 --> 1:31:17.286
What's that to do with poetry?

1:31:17.287 --> 1:31:20.039
11.47 is 11.5

1:31:20.040 --> 1:31:22.000
Who gave you your grade?

1:31:22.001 --> 1:31:24.169
You shouldn't have it yet

1:31:24.170 --> 1:31:26.964
Esmeralda told me

1:31:26.965 --> 1:31:28.882
So the class reps

1:31:28.883 --> 1:31:30.633
...did do something after all

1:31:30.760 --> 1:31:33.231
I took a load of notes!

1:31:33.388 --> 1:31:35.765
I got the impression you weren't

1:31:35.766 --> 1:31:38.309
...really following the meeting
- I noted all!

1:31:38.310 --> 1:31:40.311
Louise, I'm delighted
you've done

1:31:40.312 --> 1:31:42.230
a good job passing on information...

1:31:42.231 --> 1:31:45.276
Let's get back to this poem

1:31:45.568 --> 1:31:49.530
The rule is to count
in front of a consonant...

1:31:49.531 --> 1:31:50.874
A question

1:31:51.157 --> 1:31:52.501
What?

1:31:52.534 --> 1:31:55.244
I heard you really wiped me out

1:31:55.245 --> 1:31:57.413
...at the meeting yesterday

1:31:57.414 --> 1:31:59.499
Another remark about poetry, I see.

1:31:59.500 --> 1:32:01.960
No, it isn’t

1:32:01.961 --> 1:32:05.888
Yes, I know it isn’t about poetry

1:32:05.965 --> 1:32:07.309
What do you mean?

1:32:07.425 --> 1:32:10.985
I dunno. You wiped me out

1:32:12.097 --> 1:32:16.142
Some teachers, not me,

1:32:16.143 --> 1:32:17.481
...said if you carry on like this

1:32:17.519 --> 1:32:21.314
you'll be in trouble,

1:32:21.315 --> 1:32:24.153
...not wiped out.

1:32:24.360 --> 1:32:28.363
That's revenge. I don't get it
Why do for revenge?

1:32:28.364 --> 1:32:30.574
How come it's revenge?

1:32:30.575 --> 1:32:35.913
If you say stuff about me
getting in trouble, that's revenge

1:32:35.914 --> 1:32:39.225
It's not revenge at all

1:32:40.169 --> 1:32:42.087
We're not on the streets

1:32:42.088 --> 1:32:45.424
It's a warning
Our goal here isn't revenge,

1:32:45.425 --> 1:32:48.886
...it's discipline

1:32:48.887 --> 1:32:51.358
- Get the difference?
- I don't get it.

1:32:51.681 --> 1:32:55.226
When a judge sends someone to jail,

1:32:55.227 --> 1:32:58.021
...he doesn't do it to get revenge

1:32:58.022 --> 1:33:00.860
...It helps society run smoothly

1:33:01.025 --> 1:33:04.528
You just want revenge.
You're riffed with me.

1:33:04.529 --> 1:33:06.655
All I care about is revenge?

1:33:06.656 --> 1:33:10.242
I wake up and say
I'll get Souleymane today?

1:33:10.243 --> 1:33:12.476
You insulted him yesterday anyhow.

1:33:12.477 --> 1:33:15.289
He really laid into you!

1:33:15.290 --> 1:33:16.374
I did not.

1:33:16.375 --> 1:33:18.331
What did he say, Louise?

1:33:18.752 --> 1:33:20.837
That you we’re limited.

1:33:20.838 --> 1:33:22.631
...I underlined it, I was so shocked

1:33:22.632 --> 1:33:26.044
Me? Limited?

1:33:28.388 --> 1:33:30.711
Brilliant...

1:33:41.861 --> 1:33:43.945
Esmeralda, Louise,

1:33:43.946 --> 1:33:48.200
...What's your role as class reps?
You represent the students

1:33:48.201 --> 1:33:50.828
to help this class work
or you stir up trouble for me?

1:33:50.829 --> 1:33:52.538
We just do our job.

1:33:52.539 --> 1:33:53.831
Wicked!

1:33:53.832 --> 1:33:55.744
We report on the meeting.

1:33:55.793 --> 1:33:56.557
Of course.

1:33:56.710 --> 1:33:58.667
I didn't realize

1:33:58.671 --> 1:34:00.922
When I saw you snigger

1:34:00.923 --> 1:34:04.092
...at the meeting, I felt bad for you

1:34:04.093 --> 1:34:06.678
It wasn't the place or time

1:34:06.679 --> 1:34:08.165
It didn't look very serious

1:34:09.724 --> 1:34:11.268
Nobody minded in any case

1:34:11.309 --> 1:34:12.601
- They did!
- Only you

1:34:12.602 --> 1:34:16.230
No, it bothered me and I think

1:34:16.231 --> 1:34:18.246
it bothered the others too

1:34:18.525 --> 1:34:20.687
No. It only bothered you

1:34:22.363 --> 1:34:26.497
Sorry, but laughing like that
made you look like two skanks.

1:34:27.160 --> 1:34:29.703
What?
Have you just lost it?

1:34:29.704 --> 1:34:31.048
That's a bad thing!

1:34:33.834 --> 1:34:35.216
You can't dump on us

1:34:35.377 --> 1:34:37.170
The word is insult.

1:34:37.171 --> 1:34:39.380
You're crazy insulting on us.

1:34:39.381 --> 1:34:42.175
You say "dump on" or "insult"

1:34:42.176 --> 1:34:44.761
It's either one or the other, ok.

1:34:44.762 --> 1:34:47.097
Yeah keep on talking!

1:34:47.098 --> 1:34:49.767
In fact I never said
you we’re skanks,

1:34:49.768 --> 1:34:51.185
...I said that at one point

1:34:51.186 --> 1:34:53.521
...in the meeting

1:34:53.522 --> 1:34:56.107
...you acted like skanks.
Understand?

1:34:56.108 --> 1:34:59.235
Don't try to con us,
you said skanks

1:34:59.236 --> 1:35:01.947
I'm just explaining the difference.

1:35:01.948 --> 1:35:04.199
Sir, you don't talk to girls like that!

1:35:04.200 --> 1:35:07.035
Look who's talking!

1:35:07.036 --> 1:35:08.620
...You always insult everybody!

1:35:08.621 --> 1:35:10.581
He wants revenge on the girls

1:35:10.582 --> 1:35:14.710
No way. The noble knight
riding to rescue act,

1:35:14.711 --> 1:35:15.878
...won’t wash!

1:35:15.879 --> 1:35:18.131
You don’t talk to me, man!

1:35:18.132 --> 1:35:20.425
Show some respect!

1:35:20.426 --> 1:35:22.177
I will if I want!

1:35:22.178 --> 1:35:24.221
You're heading for trouble!

1:35:24.222 --> 1:35:25.597
Think you're tough?

1:35:25.598 --> 1:35:28.908
It's a question of discipline!

1:35:29.310 --> 1:35:30.394
I'll take you anytime!

1:35:30.395 --> 1:35:32.021
Stop playing the big short

1:35:32.022 --> 1:35:35.107
- Calm down
- Stay outta this

1:35:35.108 --> 1:35:36.192
Cut it out!

1:35:36.193 --> 1:35:37.860
Don't touch me!

1:35:37.861 --> 1:35:40.613
Don’t touch me.

1:35:40.614 --> 1:35:42.824
You're crazy!

1:35:42.825 --> 1:35:45.149
Cut it out

1:35:47.080 --> 1:35:48.872
What are you doing?

1:35:48.873 --> 1:35:49.799
I'm outta here

1:35:49.916 --> 1:35:52.418
You can't just walk out of my class.

1:35:52.419 --> 1:35:54.045
Are you nuts?

1:35:54.046 --> 1:35:56.172
- Calm down
- Let go of me

1:35:56.173 --> 1:35:57.516
Stop it

1:35:57.591 --> 1:35:59.606
- Let me go
- Ah!

1:36:00.678 --> 1:36:03.096
- Where are you going?
- Let go, fucker

1:36:03.097 --> 1:36:04.441
Pathetic

1:36:16.153 --> 1:36:17.496
Fuck

1:36:30.168 --> 1:36:33.052
What do we do?

1:36:34.214 --> 1:36:39.052
I think we need to convene
the disciplinary committee

1:36:39.053 --> 1:36:41.054
This is starting to add up
it begins

1:36:41.055 --> 1:36:44.015
with disrespect, then the fight,

1:36:44.016 --> 1:36:48.503
...with a student injured,

1:36:48.688 --> 1:36:52.316
...and finally he leaves the class
without permission.

1:36:52.317 --> 1:36:56.446
There was only one incident
and it all spread out from there.

1:36:56.447 --> 1:36:58.489
One thing led to another,

1:36:58.490 --> 1:37:00.505
...a chain reaction.

1:37:00.576 --> 1:37:01.868
Well

1:37:01.869 --> 1:37:05.414
...what I can do is take
a protective measure

1:37:05.415 --> 1:37:07.624
...since this is so serious

1:37:07.625 --> 1:37:11.545
...by suspending Souleymane
for 48 hours.

1:37:11.546 --> 1:37:13.839
That'll give us a little time

1:37:13.840 --> 1:37:16.342
...to reach a decision

1:37:16.343 --> 1:37:17.829
OK.

1:37:18.262 --> 1:37:20.276
Shall we do that?

1:37:20.306 --> 1:37:23.600
However, I need to see you tomorrow.

1:37:23.601 --> 1:37:26.228
Could you come to my office?

1:37:26.229 --> 1:37:29.171
- Good bye.
- Good bye

1:37:30.317 --> 1:37:31.860
Francois!

1:37:33.362 --> 1:37:35.936
I need a word with you

1:37:36.156 --> 1:37:39.200
There's a rumor going around...

1:37:39.201 --> 1:37:41.411
A rumor?

1:37:41.412 --> 1:37:45.957
Some students came to see me
and told me...

1:37:48.169 --> 1:37:50.126
...you insulted them

1:37:52.674 --> 1:37:54.675
Who? Louise and Esmeralda?

1:37:54.676 --> 1:37:56.302
They told me

1:37:56.303 --> 1:37:58.263
...you called them skanks

1:37:58.264 --> 1:38:00.140
...and that led to the incident

1:38:00.141 --> 1:38:01.891
...with Souleymane

1:38:01.892 --> 1:38:04.352
And you believe them?

1:38:04.353 --> 1:38:06.730
That's why I needed to see you.

1:38:06.731 --> 1:38:10.359
You didn't mention it
in your incident report...

1:38:10.360 --> 1:38:14.113
I didn't mention it.
What can I say?

1:38:14.114 --> 1:38:16.407
- Did you do it or not?
- What?

1:38:16.408 --> 1:38:18.242
- Did you...
- Hi!

1:38:18.243 --> 1:38:19.685
Hi.

1:38:19.912 --> 1:38:21.913
Did you call them skanks?

1:38:21.914 --> 1:38:24.332
But Souleymane's another matter!

1:38:24.333 --> 1:38:27.294
I know it had nothing to do with him

1:38:27.295 --> 1:38:30.047
But word's getting around.

1:38:30.048 --> 1:38:32.341
People are talking.
I wanted

1:38:32.342 --> 1:38:35.755
...to let you know
- Thanks for letting me know.

1:38:47.066 --> 1:38:49.902
Hey, you two
You complained about me.

1:38:49.903 --> 1:38:52.477
- Thanks a lot!
- You’re welcome

1:38:52.656 --> 1:38:54.824
You could have talked to me

1:38:54.825 --> 1:38:58.494
Teachers can complain about us
and vice versa, right?

1:38:58.495 --> 1:39:00.348
No, it doesn't work both ways.

1:39:02.625 --> 1:39:04.418
What are you after?

1:39:04.419 --> 1:39:05.801
To see you punished

1:39:05.837 --> 1:39:07.462
- Punished?
- Yes!

1:39:07.463 --> 1:39:11.175
- You, punish me?
- You insulted us, you get punished.

1:39:11.176 --> 1:39:13.052
Where will that get you?

1:39:13.053 --> 1:39:14.720
I'll have spoken out.

1:39:14.721 --> 1:39:17.557
Great, that's a lot of use.

1:39:17.558 --> 1:39:19.726
Do you know what 'skank' means?

1:39:19.727 --> 1:39:22.463
I never called you skanks!

1:39:22.688 --> 1:39:25.218
Yes, you did. For me
skank means prostitute.

1:39:26.901 --> 1:39:28.736
It's not that at all

1:39:28.737 --> 1:39:30.404
For me, it doesn't mean that.

1:39:30.405 --> 1:39:33.199
It's nothing important at all,

1:39:33.200 --> 1:39:36.953
just a girl laughing stupidly

1:39:36.954 --> 1:39:40.205
Hey, skank means prostitute, right?

1:39:40.249 --> 1:39:42.292
You bet!

1:39:42.293 --> 1:39:44.377
- Will Souleymane get expelled?
- No.

1:39:44.378 --> 1:39:47.005
- A disciplinary hearing?
- We don't know yet.

1:39:47.006 --> 1:39:49.299
It's a possibility

1:39:49.300 --> 1:39:52.470
Stop yelling
before anything is decided

1:39:52.471 --> 1:39:55.306
It's all settled anyway

1:39:55.307 --> 1:39:59.435
- Why say that?
- Because it's always the same!

1:39:59.436 --> 1:40:00.770
You're in no position to talk.

1:40:00.771 --> 1:40:04.900
You're the one who got hurt

1:40:04.901 --> 1:40:06.902
He didn't mean it

1:40:06.903 --> 1:40:08.821
There was a metal thing in his bag

1:40:08.822 --> 1:40:12.241
In any case he blew a fuse
and that's bad

1:40:12.242 --> 1:40:13.325
Sir,

1:40:13.326 --> 1:40:14.952
...anyone can blow a fuse

1:40:14.953 --> 1:40:16.954
And then calm down after

1:40:16.955 --> 1:40:18.206
That's not sure

1:40:18.207 --> 1:40:20.083
- You did
- No!

1:40:20.084 --> 1:40:21.427
You're calmer now

1:40:21.544 --> 1:40:23.587
I'm not. You don’t know me!

1:40:23.588 --> 1:40:26.173
All the teachers say
your attitude is perfect now...

1:40:26.174 --> 1:40:30.146
You think you've tamed me?

1:40:30.178 --> 1:40:31.554
No, being sent here helped

1:40:31.555 --> 1:40:35.423
...you understand things, see?

1:40:38.187 --> 1:40:41.648
Teachers helped you

1:40:41.649 --> 1:40:44.192
and we'll do the same
for Souleymane.

1:40:44.193 --> 1:40:48.945
I say teachers who
expel students are fuckers

1:40:51.034 --> 1:40:53.285
Right on.
You want to repeat that?

1:40:53.286 --> 1:40:56.205
- Yeah, fuckers
- Everyone goes wild

1:40:56.206 --> 1:40:58.625
...over some word I said. You
say fucker and I shouldn't react?

1:40:58.626 --> 1:40:59.918
They're fuckers!

1:40:59.919 --> 1:41:02.390
Cut it out!

1:41:02.463 --> 1:41:07.092
You say skanks, we say fucker.
It's the same thing

1:41:07.093 --> 1:41:08.969
They're nothing alike

1:41:08.970 --> 1:41:12.556
A teacher can say certain things
that students can't say.

1:41:12.557 --> 1:41:15.101
Try to understand that!

1:41:15.102 --> 1:41:16.686
We have no right to speak?

1:41:16.687 --> 1:41:20.356
You keep talking all the time!
You never stop speaking

1:41:20.357 --> 1:41:22.734
Whenever we talk, you yell.
What is this?

1:41:22.735 --> 1:41:24.853
Enough...

1:41:32.621 --> 1:41:34.577
Sir!

1:41:36.417 --> 1:41:39.093
- Sir?
- What?

1:41:41.088 --> 1:41:44.398
Will Souleymane get a hearing?

1:41:44.509 --> 1:41:46.627
Give it a rest

1:41:47.220 --> 1:41:50.014
You sound like you want
him to. It fires you up.

1:41:50.015 --> 1:41:53.839
You know what'll happen
if he's expelled?

1:41:53.894 --> 1:41:55.770
He'll change schools.

1:41:55.771 --> 1:41:57.689
No, he won’t change schools.

1:41:57.690 --> 1:42:00.734
It's automatic. It's obligatory.

1:42:00.735 --> 1:42:02.853
That goes for Souleymane too.

1:42:03.821 --> 1:42:06.114
Do you know his father?

1:42:06.115 --> 1:42:08.277
I've seen him once or twice.

1:42:08.284 --> 1:42:09.785
No, you don’t know him!

1:42:09.786 --> 1:42:13.140
If he's expelled, his dad'll
send him back to their village

1:42:13.707 --> 1:42:15.663
Don't get overdramatic

1:42:16.210 --> 1:42:18.328
He'll go back to Mali

1:42:18.504 --> 1:42:22.122
I think we all need
to keep our heads.

1:42:22.592 --> 1:42:23.935
Don’t worry

1:42:37.191 --> 1:42:39.558
You can’t smoke here sir

1:42:41.153 --> 1:42:43.683
I know, but since I was alone

1:43:06.973 --> 1:43:10.267
Ok, you went too far
with those girls.

1:43:10.268 --> 1:43:11.894
We all screw up.

1:43:11.895 --> 1:43:13.980
Souleymane overreacted.

1:43:13.981 --> 1:43:15.314
He's right.

1:43:15.315 --> 1:43:18.443
I saw Khoumba.
Her face was all bloody

1:43:18.444 --> 1:43:20.862
What he did is unacceptable.

1:43:20.863 --> 1:43:22.245
That's for sure.

1:43:22.490 --> 1:43:24.408
I know that.

1:43:24.409 --> 1:43:27.578
His bag hit her by accident.

1:43:27.579 --> 1:43:31.506
A split eybrow bleeds a lot.
That's all.

1:43:31.750 --> 1:43:34.168
You can't ignore it.

1:43:34.169 --> 1:43:39.340
Don't take it to heart.
Seen how they talk to us?

1:43:39.341 --> 1:43:42.928
How's that relevant?
Souleymane is going to get expelled

1:43:42.929 --> 1:43:45.458
...That’s it!

1:43:46.224 --> 1:43:49.107
- No.
- That's kind of logical.

1:43:52.606 --> 1:43:56.166
How many hearings last year?

1:43:58.362 --> 1:44:00.480
12 at least.

1:44:00.740 --> 1:44:02.449
Not that many.

1:44:02.450 --> 1:44:03.533
He could be right.

1:44:03.534 --> 1:44:07.496
I know, I'm on the committee
so I saw them all

1:44:07.497 --> 1:44:12.454
An average of two per month,
12 in all with an expulsion each time

1:44:12.753 --> 1:44:16.214
The hearing is where
we talk things over

1:44:16.215 --> 1:44:19.342
Ok, 12 students were expelled

1:44:19.343 --> 1:44:22.285
but maybe there was no other solution.

1:44:22.346 --> 1:44:25.807
12 out of 12

1:44:25.808 --> 1:44:28.727
...talk about debate!

1:44:28.728 --> 1:44:31.689
But 12 out of 12 just means

1:44:31.690 --> 1:44:36.110
...when a student has a hearing,
it's too late.

1:44:36.111 --> 1:44:37.612
Or it was justified.

1:44:37.613 --> 1:44:40.907
Ok, things happen
that lead to a hearing

1:44:40.908 --> 1:44:43.118
But then what happens?

1:44:43.119 --> 1:44:45.787
What do we expect from a hearing?

1:44:45.788 --> 1:44:47.581
There are prior stages:

1:44:47.582 --> 1:44:50.709
Pre-disciplinary committees,

1:44:50.710 --> 1:44:54.535
...we inform the parents,
the students are warned...

1:44:54.798 --> 1:44:58.176
- Not in this case.
- We've no time.

1:44:58.177 --> 1:45:00.428
It's pretty rare.

1:45:00.429 --> 1:45:04.725
It's rare because we have
this final punishment

1:45:04.726 --> 1:45:07.811
...that allows us to ignore
the prior steps.

1:45:07.812 --> 1:45:11.166
And even if we did use them,

1:45:11.191 --> 1:45:14.751
...the simple fact
of expelling a student...

1:45:14.861 --> 1:45:19.240
...is a disavowal
of everything we have tried.

1:45:19.241 --> 1:45:23.245
Ok, but it's Souleymane's chance
to justify himself

1:45:23.246 --> 1:45:26.123
At a hearing, you don't speak.

1:45:26.124 --> 1:45:29.168
You're scared. You're paralyzed.

1:45:29.169 --> 1:45:30.586
Exactly.

1:45:30.587 --> 1:45:32.880
Let me sum up.

1:45:32.881 --> 1:45:36.843
He'll get a disciplinary hearing,
he'll be expelled

1:45:36.844 --> 1:45:39.679
and maybe even sent back to Mali

1:45:39.680 --> 1:45:41.931
You're being overdramatic.

1:45:41.932 --> 1:45:43.850
No, I'm not

1:45:43.851 --> 1:45:47.479
Students who know him better
than any of us here,

1:45:47.480 --> 1:45:52.026
...who know his father,
say that he is likely Mali...

1:45:52.027 --> 1:45:54.248
to send him back to Mali after this

1:45:55.239 --> 1:45:58.180
Some are threatened

1:45:58.367 --> 1:46:01.536
...with boarding school
but in never happens

1:46:01.537 --> 1:46:03.759
It can happen.

1:46:03.789 --> 1:46:07.835
A lot of parents spend their time

1:46:07.836 --> 1:46:12.381
...threatening their kids with that.
You can't take it into account

1:46:12.382 --> 1:46:17.804
- Even if there was just a slight risk
that a hearing could lead

1:46:17.805 --> 1:46:22.292
to him being sent back,
I don't think I can take that risk.

1:46:24.020 --> 1:46:26.229
It's like when you hesitate

1:46:26.230 --> 1:46:29.191
...over punishing a kid
because when he goes home,

1:46:29.192 --> 1:46:31.694
once that door closes,

1:46:31.695 --> 1:46:34.071
...he'll get a beating
from his parents

1:46:34.072 --> 1:46:36.866
We've all seen that

1:46:36.867 --> 1:46:38.201
...But we still have to punish

1:46:38.202 --> 1:46:40.745
them when they go too far

1:46:40.746 --> 1:46:43.081
Whatever the consequences

1:46:43.082 --> 1:46:45.042
which don't

1:46:45.043 --> 1:46:47.044
...concern you!

1:46:47.045 --> 1:46:48.879
So I ignore that?

1:46:48.880 --> 1:46:51.882
I know punishment
can have such a consequence,

1:46:51.883 --> 1:46:54.767
...but I turn a blind eye, is that it?

1:46:55.804 --> 1:46:58.598
You can't take it into account
in every case

1:46:58.599 --> 1:47:01.559
The violence...

1:47:01.560 --> 1:47:05.021
him being sent back...

1:47:05.022 --> 1:47:07.900
- No more Christmas presents...
- True, you have to consider it

1:47:07.901 --> 1:47:09.244
but after a while...

1:47:09.486 --> 1:47:11.779
It's a question of principle

1:47:11.780 --> 1:47:14.282
...We each have a role to play

1:47:14.283 --> 1:47:17.695
We can't substitute
ourselves for the parents

1:47:18.871 --> 1:47:21.289
Sorry, but if I rewind the movie,

1:47:21.290 --> 1:47:24.918
...it's a weird chain of events.
It starts with reprimands,

1:47:24.919 --> 1:47:28.505
...when Souleymane forget
his things, talks back.

1:47:28.506 --> 1:47:32.218
We punish him. Again and again,

1:47:32.219 --> 1:47:34.637
until a disciplinary hearing

1:47:34.638 --> 1:47:38.391
leading to who knows what
Everything gets out of hand

1:47:38.392 --> 1:47:40.935
Sure, looking at it that way

1:47:40.936 --> 1:47:43.438
it's really shocking

1:47:43.439 --> 1:47:48.235
But the school won't
expelling Souleymane

1:47:48.236 --> 1:47:51.648
He's been gone for a while

1:48:28.822 --> 1:48:32.950
Francois, I didn't
expect you so soon.

1:48:32.951 --> 1:48:36.467
Have you reached a decision?

1:48:36.538 --> 1:48:40.260
I don't think I have much choice.

1:48:45.256 --> 1:48:47.299
By the way, Julie told me...

1:48:47.300 --> 1:48:50.594
you had a heated exchange

1:48:50.595 --> 1:48:52.888
...with two girls in your class.

1:48:52.889 --> 1:48:56.726
Yes, the two class reps
but it happened first so

1:48:56.727 --> 1:48:59.979
You apparently
called them "skanks"

1:48:59.980 --> 1:49:01.982
Let's say that, yes

1:49:01.983 --> 1:49:06.361
That complicates things,
but the problem remains.

1:49:06.362 --> 1:49:09.490
I'd like you to mention it
in your report

1:49:09.491 --> 1:49:14.078
I don't want it used against us
at the disciplinary hearing.

1:49:14.079 --> 1:49:17.457
Don't bother hiding it,
just write it down.

1:49:17.458 --> 1:49:19.267
I understand.

1:49:20.878 --> 1:49:23.421
I'll let you reread this

1:49:23.422 --> 1:49:26.466
before we launch the procedure.

1:49:26.467 --> 1:49:29.553
So I... I just need to add...

1:49:29.554 --> 1:49:32.805
Yes, without going into detail.

1:49:33.475 --> 1:49:35.142
Does that suit you?

1:49:35.143 --> 1:49:36.687
OK.

1:50:05.385 --> 1:50:09.357
Can you take the minute.

1:50:22.486 --> 1:50:24.192
- Hello
- Hello.

1:50:24.822 --> 1:50:26.365
Hello, sir.

1:50:26.366 --> 1:50:28.793
- Please sit down.
- Thanks.

1:51:03.739 --> 1:51:07.784
"Carl tried to reason with him,
but Souleyman broke free,"

1:51:07.785 --> 1:51:10.955
"winging his bag that hit Khoumba
in the face."

1:51:10.956 --> 1:51:14.458
"He left, insulting everyone
and slamming the door."

1:51:14.459 --> 1:51:17.754
"I didn't go after him
because I needed..."

1:51:17.755 --> 1:51:21.466
"to help Khoumba
whose eybrow was bleeding."

1:51:21.467 --> 1:51:25.429
Those are the facts
that led to today's hearing

1:51:25.430 --> 1:51:29.642
Madame, it doesn't mean
Souleyman is a bad boy.

1:51:29.643 --> 1:51:32.019
That's not we're saying

1:51:32.020 --> 1:51:34.897
But, sometimes,
a student in a class

1:51:34.898 --> 1:51:38.776
through voluntary or
involuntary behavior,

1:51:38.777 --> 1:51:41.196
can create an atmosphere that...

1:51:41.197 --> 1:51:44.388
...prevents the class from working.

1:51:58.716 --> 1:52:02.232
Do you understand
what we're saying?

1:52:03.221 --> 1:52:04.805
If I may say something, it's true

1:52:04.806 --> 1:52:07.349
there had been number of signs

1:52:07.350 --> 1:52:10.394
that should have warned us.

1:52:10.395 --> 1:52:13.381
We could have reacted sooner

1:52:13.940 --> 1:52:17.735
But how we have to deal
with an incident

1:52:17.736 --> 1:52:20.113
that is fairy violent

1:52:20.114 --> 1:52:22.490
and that's simply unacceptable.

1:52:22.491 --> 1:52:27.287
I'd like to know
if you realize that, Souleymane?

1:52:30.208 --> 1:52:34.170
We're not saying you're
deliberately violent.

1:52:34.171 --> 1:52:37.715
The problem is you can't control
what you say,

1:52:37.716 --> 1:52:39.834
...and what you do

1:52:41.095 --> 1:52:43.763
You're here to express
your point of view.

1:52:43.764 --> 1:52:47.935
Go ahead

1:52:47.936 --> 1:52:51.188
I don't give a damn.
I've got nothing to say

1:52:51.189 --> 1:52:53.455
Do whatever you want to do

1:53:03.619 --> 1:53:05.532
Excuse me...

1:53:15.215 --> 1:53:17.068
Can you translate?

1:53:17.843 --> 1:53:20.476
She says I'm a good boy

1:53:22.682 --> 1:53:24.270
I do my homework.

1:53:30.690 --> 1:53:36.119
I help my brothers and sisters
with their work when I can

1:53:40.576 --> 1:53:46.108
I always wash the dishes
and help her when I can

1:53:48.001 --> 1:53:52.004
We don't doubt he's a good son.
That's not the problem.

1:53:52.005 --> 1:53:53.673
Let's consider

1:53:53.674 --> 1:53:55.591
...his school record

1:53:55.592 --> 1:53:58.970
Excuse me, but could we focus
on the facts here?

1:53:58.971 --> 1:54:01.848
Firstly, I'd like to say

1:54:01.849 --> 1:54:06.520
...that we're surprised to see
the teacher involved in the incident

1:54:06.521 --> 1:54:08.397
...on this committee

1:54:08.398 --> 1:54:11.074
We find it highly irregular

1:54:12.652 --> 1:54:15.963
It's true. It's odd
to be both judge and litigant.

1:54:16.156 --> 1:54:17.657
First of all,

1:54:17.658 --> 1:54:21.286
...Mr. Marin was elected
to the administrative board.

1:54:21.287 --> 1:54:23.747
as the teachers' representative

1:54:23.748 --> 1:54:28.001
Moreover, I think
that the incident...

1:54:28.002 --> 1:54:30.421
...that occurred in
Mr. Marin's class

1:54:30.422 --> 1:54:33.299
...doesn't involve the teacher
directly.

1:54:33.300 --> 1:54:35.510
I'm sorry, you mention

1:54:35.511 --> 1:54:38.638
...some harsh words

1:54:38.639 --> 1:54:40.181
...spoken by the teacher...

1:54:40.182 --> 1:54:43.143
Apparently, you used
the word "skanks"

1:54:43.144 --> 1:54:46.021
...to describe the class reps.
And that's a problem

1:54:46.022 --> 1:54:47.648
I did say that

1:54:47.649 --> 1:54:50.943
...but it wasn’t something
that concerned Souleymane.

1:54:50.944 --> 1:54:55.031
I think he used the excuse
of a rather heated exchange

1:54:55.032 --> 1:54:57.075
...to express the bad mood

1:54:57.076 --> 1:55:00.745
that he was in that day.

1:55:00.746 --> 1:55:02.539
He tried to defend them

1:55:02.540 --> 1:55:04.958
So I feel that it's relevant

1:55:04.959 --> 1:55:08.045
Sorry, but absolutely
nothing justifies

1:55:08.046 --> 1:55:11.173
...being disrespectful to a teacher,

1:55:11.174 --> 1:55:16.234
...insulting everyone and leaving
a class without permission.

1:55:17.765 --> 1:55:20.956
Souleymane, do you
have anything to say?

1:55:21.978 --> 1:55:24.714
I don't know. What can I say?

1:55:34.700 --> 1:55:36.347
Souleymane?

1:55:38.662 --> 1:55:42.531
- What did she say?
- The same thing again

1:55:53.136 --> 1:55:54.886
Souleymane?

1:55:55.430 --> 1:55:58.269
She apologizes on my behalf.

1:57:03.337 --> 1:57:05.970
You can come back in now.

1:57:28.865 --> 1:57:31.617
Madame, the committee
has conferred

1:57:31.618 --> 1:57:35.705
and has decided to expel Souleymane
from the school for good.

1:57:35.706 --> 1:57:39.417
You will receive the ruling
by registered mail

1:57:39.418 --> 1:57:42.463
...and have eight days to appeal,

1:57:49.971 --> 1:57:55.134
We shall do our best to find
Souleymane another school

1:57:57.938 --> 1:58:00.365
Goodbye, Messieurs, Mesdames

1:58:03.444 --> 1:58:09.181
Souleymane, come to see me
before the end of the week, please.

1:58:41.110 --> 1:58:43.125
Mathematical proportionality.

1:58:44.322 --> 1:58:49.493
This year, you learned
mathematical proportionality?

1:58:49.494 --> 1:58:53.706
- I liked science
- What you learned, not liked.

1:58:53.707 --> 1:58:56.584
If you liked it, you learned.

1:58:56.585 --> 1:58:58.703
So what did you learn?

1:58:59.046 --> 1:59:03.008
All about volcanoes, earthquakes,

1:59:03.009 --> 1:59:04.801
...plates...

1:59:04.802 --> 1:59:07.429
Convergence and divergence,

1:59:07.430 --> 1:59:10.946
...movement of the Earth's plates,

1:59:11.518 --> 1:59:13.853
- It was fascinating.
- It interested you?

1:59:13.854 --> 1:59:15.296
- Yeah.
- Good.

1:59:15.981 --> 1:59:20.026
Well, in mathematics,

1:59:20.027 --> 1:59:22.487
.. trigonometry Pythagoras
theorem, Thales theorem.

1:59:22.488 --> 1:59:24.322
I'll stop you there.

1:59:24.323 --> 1:59:27.743
You can't sit there and brag...

1:59:27.744 --> 1:59:30.495
...you learned Pythagoras theorem.
Recite it for us

1:59:33.875 --> 1:59:35.877
If, in a triangle

1:59:35.878 --> 1:59:40.131
...two sides are equal to

1:59:40.132 --> 1:59:42.509
...If the square rot

1:59:42.510 --> 1:59:44.177
If the square of two sides

1:59:44.178 --> 1:59:48.105
is equal to the square

1:59:48.224 --> 1:59:50.976
...the square of the hypotenuse

1:59:50.977 --> 1:59:53.199
then the triangle's a rectangle.

1:59:53.814 --> 1:59:55.773
More or less, yes

1:59:55.774 --> 1:59:57.316
It's spot on

1:59:57.317 --> 2:00:00.570
All right. I believe you.

2:00:00.571 --> 2:00:03.657
In history, I learned
about triangular trade.

2:00:03.658 --> 2:00:09.086
The fact that ships left Europe...

2:00:09.497 --> 2:00:13.709
...with manufactured goods that
they took to Africa to trade for men,

2:00:13.710 --> 2:00:16.587
...who’d became slaves
that they took to America to work.

2:00:16.588 --> 2:00:20.216
Then they took the money
they made back to Europe.

2:00:20.217 --> 2:00:22.747
That's triangular trade

2:00:23.429 --> 2:00:25.013
Chemistry

2:00:25.014 --> 2:00:27.176
What in chemistry?

2:00:27.225 --> 2:00:29.078
Combustion

2:00:29.269 --> 2:00:30.686
What's that?

2:00:30.687 --> 2:00:35.149
Blending Fehling's solution
and glucose.

2:00:35.150 --> 2:00:36.494
What do you get?

2:00:36.944 --> 2:00:39.696
Heat up test-tube,

2:00:39.697 --> 2:00:41.918
...and it changes color.

2:00:43.284 --> 2:00:46.370
- What's the interest?
- The interest?

2:00:46.371 --> 2:00:51.902
I dunno. Why teach it to us
if there's no interest?

2:00:52.085 --> 2:00:53.835
Reproduction

2:00:55.422 --> 2:00:59.133
What did you learn
about human reproduction?

2:00:59.134 --> 2:01:01.091
Human reproduction...

2:01:01.095 --> 2:01:03.669
Well, the sperm

2:01:03.848 --> 2:01:05.657
...gets into the ovum

2:01:05.683 --> 2:01:07.559
then you wait 9 months,

2:01:07.560 --> 2:01:11.840
then you do a sonogram
and then it comes out

2:01:11.898 --> 2:01:13.281
The sperm does?

2:01:13.400 --> 2:01:14.743
No, the baby

2:01:15.360 --> 2:01:17.993
The human being that's inside.

2:01:18.113 --> 2:01:20.335
- Khoumba?
- Me?

2:01:20.533 --> 2:01:22.659
Yes. That is your name?

2:01:22.660 --> 2:01:24.042
Yes.

2:01:26.039 --> 2:01:30.937
In music, I learned to play
the alto recorder...

2:01:31.044 --> 2:01:33.000
and in Spanish

2:01:33.463 --> 2:01:35.131
The recorder in Spanish?

2:01:35.132 --> 2:01:37.759
No, in music, I learned

2:01:37.760 --> 2:01:40.678
to play the alto recorder.
- Right

2:01:40.679 --> 2:01:42.889
- And other stuff in Spanish
- Good.

2:01:42.890 --> 2:01:46.141
Can you say something
to us in Spanish?

2:01:53.986 --> 2:01:58.472
- And that means?
- "It's the vacation soon".

2:02:01.619 --> 2:02:03.781
I didn't learn anything

2:02:04.789 --> 2:02:09.460
You cant spend 9 months at
school and not learn anything.

2:02:09.461 --> 2:02:12.421
I'm the living proof

2:02:12.422 --> 2:02:15.174
You got something
from the books we read.

2:02:15.175 --> 2:02:17.427
- Your books are shite.
- They're what?

2:02:17.428 --> 2:02:19.340
They're useless.

2:02:19.889 --> 2:02:23.713
What about a book
you read by yourself?

2:02:24.936 --> 2:02:27.020
The books I read?

2:02:27.021 --> 2:02:30.213
Well, there's The Republic

2:02:33.695 --> 2:02:35.078
Platon’s "Republic"?

2:02:35.405 --> 2:02:38.818
You read that?

2:02:39.326 --> 2:02:40.914
How come?

2:02:41.495 --> 2:02:44.706
My big sister had it

2:02:44.707 --> 2:02:47.752
- She does philosophy?
- No, law

2:02:48.378 --> 2:02:50.025
So what's it about?

2:02:50.380 --> 2:02:53.425
Well, there's this guy...

2:02:53.550 --> 2:02:54.992
His name's Socrates

2:02:55.010 --> 2:02:56.716
Yeah, Socrates.

2:02:58.055 --> 2:03:02.394
He stops people in the street
and asks them:

2:03:02.810 --> 2:03:05.729
"Are you sure of thinking
what you think?"

2:03:05.730 --> 2:03:08.774
"Are you sure of doing
what you do? and so on?"

2:03:08.775 --> 2:03:12.027
After that, people
start getting confused.

2:03:12.028 --> 2:03:13.988
They ask questions.

2:03:13.989 --> 2:03:16.003
The guy's too much

2:03:16.200 --> 2:03:18.576
What does he ask people about?

2:03:18.577 --> 2:03:20.078
Everything.

2:03:20.079 --> 2:03:26.066
Love, religion, God
people, everything

2:03:26.461 --> 2:03:28.519
- It's good you read it
- I know

2:03:28.797 --> 2:03:31.326
It's not a skank's book!

2:03:36.930 --> 2:03:41.351
Wait a second. Before you leave,
here are your self-portraits

2:03:41.352 --> 2:03:45.397
One by one. When you have
yours, you can go.

2:03:45.398 --> 2:03:47.310
What is it?

2:03:51.530 --> 2:03:52.988
What is it?

2:03:52.989 --> 2:03:56.284
These are the self-portraits
that you wrote

2:03:56.285 --> 2:03:59.120
...and that we made up
with the class photo and so on

2:03:59.121 --> 2:04:00.665
You too, Eva.

2:04:03.042 --> 2:04:04.792
You don't have one?

2:04:07.171 --> 2:04:10.341
- You look good in it
- Cut it out

2:04:10.342 --> 2:04:13.344
You're like a leader

2:04:13.345 --> 2:04:15.257
Very good.

2:04:16.098 --> 2:04:18.260
- Good bye, Sir.
- Good bye.

2:04:19.310 --> 2:04:22.295
- Have a good vacation.
- You too

2:04:28.611 --> 2:04:30.833
- Sir?
- Yes...

2:04:32.240 --> 2:04:34.358
What is it?

2:04:35.285 --> 2:04:37.403
I didn't learn anything

2:04:38.497 --> 2:04:41.174
What? That doesn't mean anything

2:04:42.418 --> 2:04:45.879
Earlier, all the others...

2:04:45.880 --> 2:04:48.925
...said they'd learned something

2:04:49.467 --> 2:04:52.247
Compared to them, I learned nothing

2:04:53.096 --> 2:04:55.264
You learned as much as them

2:04:55.265 --> 2:04:57.725
They had to think hard too.

2:04:57.726 --> 2:04:59.769
It's not easy

2:04:59.770 --> 2:05:05.233
to remember what you learned...

2:05:05.234 --> 2:05:07.249
But I don't understand

2:05:07.946 --> 2:05:09.328
What do you mean?

2:05:09.906 --> 2:05:12.533
I don't understand what we do.

2:05:12.534 --> 2:05:14.283
In French?

2:05:14.745 --> 2:05:16.450
In school

2:05:17.831 --> 2:05:22.919
You can’t say you don’t
understand everything.

2:05:22.920 --> 2:05:25.142
That’s not true...

2:05:27.801 --> 2:05:30.992
I don’t want to go
to vocational school.

2:05:31.555 --> 2:05:34.644
There’s no question of that yet

2:05:34.850 --> 2:05:37.277
You’re moving on to the next year.

2:05:37.770 --> 2:05:42.190
You’ll have plenty of time
to think about your future

2:05:42.191 --> 2:05:45.569
Vocational school isn’t
an absolute certainty

2:05:45.570 --> 2:05:48.615
It all depends on how you do next year

2:05:49.908 --> 2:05:51.613
But I don’t want to.

2:09:24.307 --> 2:09:29.323
Subtitles: Ian Burnley
